data.body:
This would be useful for packages that accept an unknown amount of user-defined values; for example, a package that would take a list of file extensions and a command to associate with them. Example data structure:

```
[
  {'extension': 'php', 'command': 'php', 'args': ''}
  {'extension': 'psc', 'command': 'PapyrusCompiler.exe', 'args': ''}
  {'extension': 'billy', 'command': 'bob', 'args': 'joe'}
  {'extension': 'foo', 'command': 'bar', 'args': 'bat'}
]
```

This could be represented in the settings page by having each object be multiple side-by-side text fields (one for each property), along with a "remove entry" button to remove the object from the array. Additionally, there'd be an "add entry" button that inserts another row with the fields with their default values.
